    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When not in water, you use a contra-gravitic levitation pack to move. It provides a walking speed of 10m, though you actually hover between 1 and 2 meters from the ground. You are immune to becoming prone and you ignore any penalties caused by difficult terrain.</p>\n<p>However, when you suffer a critical hit, you must roll a d20. On a 1 or a 2, the device malfunctions and you fall to the ground. Your walking speed becomes 0 and you are considered prone. You or another creature can use an Action to repair the pack with a successful DC 15 Intelligence (Engineering) check.</p>",
